    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Airlines Flying Nonstop from New York to London</h2>
      <p>The New York to London route is one of the most competed in global aviation. Six or more airlines offer daily nonstop service, creating genuine choice across price points and cabin classes.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>British Airways</strong> — Multiple daily from JFK to LHR with Club World business class.</li>
        <li><strong>Virgin Atlantic</strong> — From JFK and EWR to LHR and LGW with competitive Upper Class fares.</li>
        <li><strong>American Airlines</strong> — Daily from JFK to LHR, codeshares with British Airways.</li>
        <li><strong>Delta Air Lines</strong> — Multiple daily from JFK to LHR with Delta One business class.</li>
        <li><strong>United Airlines</strong> — Daily from EWR to LHR with Polaris business class.</li>
        <li><strong>Norse Atlantic</strong> — Budget nonstop from JFK to LGW at significantly lower fares.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Eastbound vs Westbound Flight Times</h2>
      <p>The eastbound flight benefits from the jet stream and takes approximately 6.5-7 hours — around 45 minutes faster than the westbound return. Overnight flights from New York arrive in London the following morning.</p>
      <div class="tip-box"><p>An overnight departure from JFK arriving at Heathrow by 7-8am is the ideal itinerary — you get a full day in London and can check into your hotel by early afternoon.</p></div>
      <h2>Tips for New York to London Nonstop</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Norse Atlantic</strong> offers the lowest base fares — often 200-300 pounds cheaper than legacy carriers for economy.</li>
        <li><strong>Business Class</strong> on this route is one of the most competed premium products in aviation. Set fare alerts for flash sales.</li>
        <li><strong>British Airways Avios</strong> redemptions from JFK to LHR are among the best-value in the program.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
